# loc-ai-proxy Configuration

This configuration enables both opencode and direct Anthropic API providers.

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Get Anthropic API Key
- Visit: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
- Create a new API key
- Copy the key (starts with "sk-ant-")

### 2. Configure the Proxy

Edit this file and add your API key:

```yaml
providers:
  anthropic:
    enabled: true
    type: anthropic
    api_key: "sk-ant-your-api-key-here"  # <-- Add your key here
```

Or set the environment variable:
```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY="sk-ant-your-api-key-here"
```

### 3. Run the Proxy

```bash
./target/debug/locaiproxy -c config.yaml
```

## Available Models

When using the Anthropic provider, you can use these model aliases:
- `claude-3-opus` → Claude 3 Opus
- `claude-3-5-sonnet` → Claude 3.5 Sonnet  
- `claude-3-5-haiku` → Claude 3.5 Haiku

Or use the full model IDs:
- `anthropic/claude-3-opus-20240229`
- `anthropic/claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022`
- `anthropic/claude-3-5-haiku-20241022`

## Current Configuration

providers:
  anthropic:
    enabled: true
    type: anthropic
    # api_key: set via ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env var or add above
